Environment: Next.js 15 App Router at sales.meavo.app (port 3002 locally). Quotes → deals tool for the MEAVO sales team; part of the meavo-booths ecosystem sharing one Neon Postgres DB with gateway/assembly/hols/mrp.

## Stack

- Next.js 15 App Router, TypeScript strict, React 19, Tailwind CSS 3
- Prisma 6 via `@meavo/db` (schema owned by meavo-db repo) → shared Neon Postgres
- NextAuth v5 JWT sessions, Google SSO only (invite-only), `ToolCardAccess` gating
- `@meavo/navigation` shared nav; Vercel hosting; Vercel Blob for product images
- Integrations: Google Sheets (Ops File), Xero Custom Connection, Frankfurter FX, VIES VAT, `@react-pdf/renderer`

## Do NOT

- Edit the Prisma schema here — it lives in meavo-db; bump the `@meavo/db` git ref instead
- Run `prisma db push` (disabled) — shared DB; use idempotent `prisma/sql/*.sql` + `prisma db execute`
- Block quote → deal conversion on Ops File / Xero failures — export functions never throw; persist error on `Deal`, offer retry
- Look up the tool card by `linkedAppKey` at runtime — use `SALES_TOOL_CARD_ID` (`seed-sales-tool`)
- Add shadcn / Radix / MUI — use the in-house kit in `src/components/ui.tsx`
- Let Xero import overwrite Sales-owned product fields (kind, families, images, availability, restrictions)
- Create a separate Quote model — quotes are `Deal` rows with `stage = QUOTE`
- Commit secrets or `.env`

## Code layout

| Area | Path |
|------|------|
| Pages (authenticated route group) | `src/app/(app)/` — deals, clients, products, quotes, settings/xero |
| Public login | `src/app/login/` |
| Server Actions (all mutations) | `src/app/actions/` |
| API routes (NextAuth + quote PDF only) | `src/app/api/` |
| Domain logic + validation | `src/lib/` (Zod in `src/lib/*-input.ts`) |
| Integrations | `src/lib/ops-sheet-export.ts`, `src/lib/sheets-client.ts`, `src/lib/xero/` |
| Auth | `src/lib/meavo-auth.ts`, `src/lib/auth.ts`, `src/lib/auth.config.ts`, `src/middleware.ts` |
| UI kit + components | `src/components/` (`ui.tsx`, `nav.tsx`) |
| Smoke scripts (no test suite) | `scripts/` — run via `npx tsx --env-file=.env scripts/<name>.ts` |

## Data flow

```
Browser → src/middleware.ts (session redirect, pages only)
        → page (requireSalesAccess / requireSalesAdmin)
        → Server Action (Zod validate → Prisma → revalidatePath)
        → on win: BoothUnit rows + non-blocking side effects
            ├─ Ops File append (googleapis, src/lib/ops-sheet-export.ts)
            └─ Xero draft invoice (src/lib/xero/export-deal.ts)
```

Every mutation that must reach the Ops File or Xero goes through `exportDealToOpsSheet()` / `exportDealToXero()`. These functions never throw: failures are stored on the `Deal` (`sheetSyncError`, `xeroSyncError`) and retried via actions in `src/app/actions/deals.ts` / `xero.ts` — external failures must never fail the user-facing write.

